As the sunrises on the week, it’s an opportunity for me to reframe, move forward, and try to be better. I am my own worst critic, as I think we all are. I truly don’t believe we’d say the things to others that we say to ourselves. Yet this self-criticism, though sometimes painful, moves me to keep “showing up.” Pictured here: Temples of Bagan, Myanmar (Burma). On the journey to attempt summiting Hkakabo Razi, Southeast Asia’s tallest mountain, the layers of mist, life, and paths to get anywhere are as complex as the landscapes before me.

